cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.SI. 

This paper deals with privacy and security issues in payment channel networks, which are commonly used in cryptocurrencies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses network topologies and optimization, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of noise mechanisms and tradeoffs between privacy and utility could also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
